dbStoredQuestions.questionText: Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a number line and use ordering and absolute value to compare numbers.

standards.description: Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a number line and use ordering and absolute value to compare numbers.
standards.subject: Mathematics

rigor.justification: The assessment items focus primarily on performing and applying integer operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division), graphing integers on a number line, and writing inequalities — all tasks that align most directly with 7.NS.A.1 (representing and comparing integers on the number line and computing with them). Problems include straightforward computation (recall/application) and some multi-step application (order of operations, prime factorization, and comparing on a number line), so overall cognitive demand is moderate (application/reasoning at DOK 2).
